{"key":"post-13158733","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13158733</id>\n<content>During colonization, small amounts of ambient room light seems to help speed things up over total darkness.&amp;nbsp; It's not a deal killer either way, but there is an advantage in colonization speed and speed to fruiting once the substrate is ready by exposing to light from day one.&amp;nbsp; Avoid direct sunlight and other types of bright light during colonization, but the old advice to colonize in total darkness is incorrect.&amp;nbsp; My colonization room has a north facing window, and this is sufficient(in the northern hemisphere.. Australians would want a south facing window)&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13159261</next>\n<prev>13158716</prev>\n<first>13158692</first>\n<last>13159261</last>\n<when>1283870941</when>\n<utime>09/07/10 05:49 PM</utime>\n</post>"}